# Markdown deliverables

When the user asks for a **PR description**, **PR body**, **commit message template**, **changelog entry**, or similar text they will paste elsewhere — put the **full content inside a single fenced markdown code block** (` ```markdown `).

## Do

- One copy-paste block with the complete body (headings, checklists, bullets intact)
- Put the PR **title** on its own line **outside** the block when helpful
- Use the project's PR template sections when proposing PRs (see `.github/pull_request_template.md`)

## Do not

- Render the PR body as normal chat prose with headings (it loses structure when copied)
- Summarize "here's what to include" instead of giving the actual markdown
- Wait for the user to say "in markdown" — **default to the fenced block** for paste-ready artifacts

## Example

**PR title:** `feat(api): add daily challenge service`

```markdown
## Summary

- First bullet
- Second bullet

## Test plan

- [x] `pnpm test:all`
```
